\par KNOWLEDGE }{\fs20\cf0 (INT; TRAINED ONLY)
\par Like the Craft and Profession skills, Knowledge actually encompasses a number of unrelated skills. Knowledge represents a study of some body of lore, possibly an academic or even scientific discipline.
\par Below are listed typical fields of study.
\par \bullet  Arcana (ancient mysteries, magic traditions, arcane symbols, cryptic phrases, constructs, dragons, magical beasts)
\par \bullet  Architecture and engineering (buildings, aqueducts, bridges, fortifications)
\par \bullet  Dungeoneering (aberrations, caverns, oozes, spelunking)
\par \bullet  Geography (lands, terrain, climate, people)
\par \bullet  History (royalty, wars, colonies, migrations, founding of cities)
\par \bullet  Local (legends, personalities, inhabitants, laws, customs, traditions, humanoids)
\par \bullet  Nature (animals, fey, giants, monstrous humanoids, plants, seasons and cycles, weather, vermin)
\par \bullet  Nobility and royalty (lineages, heraldry, family trees, mottoes, personalities)
\par \bullet  Religion (gods and goddesses, mythic history, ecclesiastic tradition, holy symbols, undead)
\par \bullet  The planes (the Inner Planes, the Outer Planes, the Astral Plane, the Ethereal Plane, outsiders, elementals, magic related to the planes)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Check:}{\fs20\cf0  Answering a question within your field of study has a DC of 10 (for really easy questions), 15 (for basic questions), or 20 to 30 (for really tough questions).
\par In many cases, you can use this skill to identify monsters and their special powers or vulnerabilities. In general, the DC of such a check equals 10 + the monster\rquote s HD. A successful check allows you to remember a bit of useful information about t
hat monster.
\par For every 5 points by which your check result exceeds the DC, you recall another piece of useful information.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Action:}{\fs20\cf0  Usually none. In most cases, making a Knowledge check doesn\rquote t take an action\emdash you simply know the answer or you don\rquote t.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Try Again:}{\fs20\cf0  No. The check represents what you know, and thinking about a topic a second time doesn\rquote t let you know something that you never learned in the first place.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Synergy:}{\fs20\cf0  If you have 5 or more ranks in Knowledge (arcana), you get a +2 bonus on Spellcraft checks.
\par If you have 5 or more ranks in Knowledge (architecture and engineering), you get a +2 bonus on Search checks made to find secret doors or hidden compartments.
\par If you have 5 or more ranks in Knowledge (geography), you get a +2 bonus on Survival checks made to keep from getting lost or to avoid natural hazards.
\par If you have 5 or more ranks in Knowledge (history), you get a +2 bonus on bardic knowledge checks.
\par If you have 5 or more ranks in Knowledge (local), you get a +2 bonus on Gather Information checks.
\par If you have 5 or more ranks in Knowledge (nature), you get a +2 bonus on Survival checks made in aboveground natural environments (aquatic, desert, forest, hill, marsh, mountains, or plains).
\par If you have 5 or more ranks in Knowledge (nobility and royalty), you get a +2 bonus on Diplomacy checks.
\par If you have 5 or more ranks in Knowledge (religion), you get a +2 bonus on turning checks against undead.
\par If you have 5 or more ranks in Knowledge (the planes), you get a +2 bonus on Survival checks made while on other planes.
\par If you have 5 or more ranks in Knowledge (dungeoneering), you get a +2 bonus on Survival checks made while underground.
\par If you have 5 or more ranks in Survival, you get a +2 bonus on Knowledge (nature) checks.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Untrained:}{\fs20\cf0  An untrained Knowledge check is simply an Intelligence check. Without actual training, you know only common knowledge (DC 10 or lower).
